Paper: hep-th/0104255

Date: 2001-04-30

Title: Background field method in the Wilson formulation

Authors: M. Bonini and E. Tricarico

Comments: LaTex 13 pages, 1 figure; to appear in Nucl.Phys.B

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B606 (2001) 231-244

A cutoff regularization for a pure Yang-Mills theory is implemented withinthe background field method keeping explicit the gauge invariance of theeffective action. The method has been applied to compute the beta function atone loop order.